body:
Fudge Adapted from the Royal Hostess Ingredients 150g flour 60ml cold water 350g sugar 385g tin condensed milk 5 ml vanilla
Combine all ingredients in a large copper-bottomed pot and stir on medium-low heat until dissolved. Boil mixture until the soft ball stage and the mixture has a deeper colour and has thickened conspicuously. This may take ~ 20 minutes. Add vanilla and stir vigourously to combine - beware of splashes. Take fudge off the heat and stir till cooled slightly. Pour into a greased 23 x 23 cm lammington tin and allow to cool Cut into squares and serve.
